rComments: Worst math professor ever, makes mistakes in lecture, rambles incomprehensible. If you haven't had experience with linear algebra before try to get enough sleep, good nutrition, maybe prayer, and a tutor, since this man will not be a help at all.

By far the worst class I've taken at the university.  He obviously knows the material but teaches almost exclusively by proofs. There will seldom be a numerical example.  Most of the class didn't attend lecture because it was useless.  Midterms were easy but final covered some material we didn't have homework on which I thought was kind of unfair.

This SOB DOESN'T CARE about teaching and students AT ALL. By "at all", I mean literally NOTHING. His exam is easy only because he told you what would be on exam beforehand, but you still have to watch out for calculation mistakes, which results from large quantity of questions. If you don't care about the class, take it, otherwise he's a nightmare.

I came on here before this past semester and saw how awful Haboush was supposed to be and thought, "Nah he can't be do bad" Wrong. This man is easily the worst professor you could possibly have. The class is taught entirely through proofs; you'll almost never see a real example. Exams are too long to finish and nothing like the homework. AVOID HIM!
These comments are soo true.  Except he DOES know his stuff.  Google: Haboush's Theorem. TERRIBLE TEACHER!!!!

He is the worst professor when it comes to teaching. His lectures are mostly useless, just a bunch of mathematical proofs without even explanation/examples of how to use or apply them, but he is quite fair in person. Do not expect any real office hours. Advice: Do not take him, if had to, pray and find someone to teach you MATH415.
Teaches applied linear algebra theoretically... proofs are used to teach this class because he is 'not an applied mathematician' his lectures are useless if you learn math through examples

DON'T TAKE PROF: Is often unprepared to teach, teaches incorrect examples (must be corrected by students), teaches from a book he even admits is a bad textbook, tries to make matrix examples on the spot (often leading to incorrect examples mentioned above). Students are simply not provided with a conductive learning atmosphere.

Had this professor for the first three weeks of Math415 and was lucky enough to be able to transfer out. This man has no idea what Linear Algebra is. He is incapable of staying on topic. Does not go over homework. Syllabus was never passed out. Non-existent office hours. Reading the textbook is your only hope if you get shafted with him. GL folks.

easily the worst professor i have ever had.  1) doesnt know his own material 2) cant teach at all 3) cant lecture because he always forgets what he is talking about 4) hypicroite-tests you on exactly what he told you he wouldnt test you on 5) truly doesnt care about the students.  I would bet that 9/10 random people on the street could teach better
Worst professor ever. Avoid.
At first was not very clear but is getting better. If you pay attention to his proofs they make sense and it helps with the homework.

professor does NOT respond to e-mails.  he teaches like he is teaching math majors doing proofs the entire time.  you will have to learn all the material on your own time.  going to class is all but useless (i know, i went to all of them.....)

teaches like he is teaching to math majors.  going to class is all but useless (trust me, i went to all the classes).  you will have to learn all the stuff out of the book on your own time.  he also does not respond to e-mails!  getting an e-mail list of people in the class is very useful if you have questions you want answered.

He is a horrible teacher because he doesn't care about teaching. He's totally bored to teach and doesn't give any homeworks, gives unannounced oral exams to avoid grading and he doesn't follow any books. He's all over the place when he teaches. I have to admit that he knows a lot of stuff, but he also likes to sound obscure. He's smart.

One of the worst teachers I have ever had. Never gave us a syllabus, no website, no schedule. NOTHING!. Lectures on one thing, the book says another, and the tests are on neither of the two. Avoid if at all posible

I can't imagine a worse professor than this man. His tests were written on scratch paper, prepard no more than an hour before class and had nothing to do with anything he talked about previously. The day he was supposed to bring the graded exams to class he "forgot" them, and decided to go back to his apt to get them. he didn't show up for an hour.
No structure or syllabus to the class, lectures boring and confusing, no clue about exams or grading or anything.  Do not take his class ever.
Terrible.  He has no structure to his class, he just goes up and talks math, and if you happen to understand, whoop de doo.  Not a good prof.
Do not take this class, he is the worst prof. Uses diferent termonology from the book, so that is useless. Makes no attempt to teach anything, and he does not even present the info clearly
